00:08:20.220 --> 00:08:21.930
Wow, very, very disturbing.

00:08:21.930 --> 00:08:24.690
Margaret Brennan for us, thank you.

00:08:24.690 --> 00:08:27.930
It was sentencing day for former Minnesota police officer

00:08:27.930 --> 00:08:30.450
found guilty of manslaughter in the shooting death

00:08:30.450 --> 00:08:32.400
of 20-year-old Daunte Wright.

00:08:32.400 --> 00:08:35.520
David Schuman from our Minneapolis station WCCO

00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:37.680
was inside the courthouse.

00:08:37.680 --> 00:08:41.100
I have to live in this nightmare, watching my son shot

00:08:41.100 --> 00:08:45.540
and killed over and over again.

00:08:45.540 --> 00:08:49.290
Through tears, Katie Wright pleaded for the former police

00:08:49.290 --> 00:08:52.290
officer Kim Potter to get the maximum sentence

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:53.670
for killing her son.

00:08:53.670 --> 00:08:55.370
She never once said his name.

00:08:55.370 --> 00:08:57.900


00:08:57.900 --> 00:09:00.870
And for that, I'll never be able to forgive you.

00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:04.170
Potter, who had been on the force for 26 years,

00:09:04.170 --> 00:09:06.750
was convicted of first-degree manslaughter

00:09:06.750 --> 00:09:09.750
two days before Christmas.

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:13.050
Potter says she meant to tase Wright during a traffic stop

00:09:13.050 --> 00:09:14.160
last April.

00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:15.290
I just shot him.

00:09:15.290 --> 00:09:17.120
I grabbed the wrong [BLEEP] gun!

00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:18.010
[BLEEP]

00:09:18.010 --> 00:09:21.330
But pulled her gun instead, shooting Wright once

00:09:21.330 --> 00:09:22.230
in the chest.

00:09:22.230 --> 00:09:25.410
When her time to speak came, a tearful Potter

00:09:25.410 --> 00:09:27.870
looked directly at Wright's mother.

00:09:27.870 --> 00:09:30.690
I understand the mother's love, and I'm

00:09:30.690 --> 00:09:33.090
sorry I broke your heart.

00:09:33.090 --> 00:09:37.980
Officer Potter made a mistake that ended tragically.

00:09:37.980 --> 00:09:41.460
In the end, Judge Regina Chu, her voice cracking,

00:09:41.460 --> 00:09:44.410
said Potter would serve 24 months,

00:09:44.410 --> 00:09:45.860
a quarter of what she faced.

00:09:45.860 --> 00:09:49.060


00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:52.540
She never intended to hurt anyone.

00:09:52.540 --> 00:09:55.510
Wright's family disappointed with the sentence.

00:09:55.510 --> 00:09:58.990
This lady got a slap on the wrist.

00:09:58.990 --> 00:10:03.460
And we still every night sitting around crying, waiting

00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:07.630
for my son to come home.

00:10:07.630 --> 00:10:09.910
Under Minnesota law, Potter will only

00:10:09.910 --> 00:10:12.370
have to serve 2/3 of her sentence

00:10:12.370 --> 00:10:14.830
in prison, 16 months, which means

00:10:14.830 --> 00:10:17.950
she could be released almost exactly two years

00:10:17.950 --> 00:10:19.720
after Daunte Wright's death.

00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:20.440
Jericka.

00:10:20.440 --> 00:10:22.940
David Schuman for us, thank you.

00:10:22.940 --> 00:10:25.720
Tonight, the entire family of America's top doctor

00:10:25.720 --> 00:10:27.070
is fighting COVID.

00:10:27.070 --> 00:10:29.590
Surgeon General Vivek Murthy revealed

00:10:29.590 --> 00:10:32.620
his four-year-old daughter's diagnosis a few days ago.

00:10:32.620 --> 00:10:35.200
Well, now, Murthy, his wife, and five-year-old son

00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:37.270
have all tested positive.

00:10:37.270 --> 00:10:40.300
We turn now to the hidden toll of the two-year pandemic

00:10:40.300 --> 00:10:42.320
on exhausted health care workers.

00:10:42.320 --> 00:10:45.320
Here's CBS's Kris Van Cleave.

00:10:45.320 --> 00:10:47.780
Those are all COVID patient rooms.

00:10:47.780 --> 00:10:49.460
Nurse Courtney Hollingsworth takes us

00:10:49.460 --> 00:10:52.580
inside the COVID surg unit at St. Claire Regional Medical

00:10:52.580 --> 00:10:54.860
Center in rural Morehead, Kentucky.

00:10:54.860 --> 00:10:56.990
Some of these people are very, very sick.

00:10:56.990 --> 00:11:00.200
Hollingsworth estimates about 40% of the nursing staff

00:11:00.200 --> 00:11:02.870
here has left during the pandemic.

00:11:02.870 --> 00:11:05.630
Burnout and what she calls compassion fatigue

00:11:05.630 --> 00:11:07.370
are now just part of the job.

00:11:07.370 --> 00:11:10.940
We're reminding ourselves why we went in to nursing,

00:11:10.940 --> 00:11:12.410
where we make a difference.

00:11:12.410 --> 00:11:15.260
The hospital says about 90% of COVID patients who

00:11:15.260 --> 00:11:17.180
end up here are unvaccinated.

00:11:17.180 --> 00:11:19.010
The staff says much of this community

00:11:19.010 --> 00:11:21.020
seems to have moved on from the pandemic

00:11:21.020 --> 00:11:23.390
while its life and death consequences play out

00:11:23.390 --> 00:11:26.240
inside the hospital walls around the clock.

00:11:26.240 --> 00:11:30.590
The only thing that is semi-comparable and not even

00:11:30.590 --> 00:11:32.570
close is like a battlefield.

00:11:32.570 --> 00:11:35.090
And we've been fighting now for two years.

00:11:35.090 --> 00:11:37.160
But we're the only people left to fight.

00:11:37.160 --> 00:11:39.380
Do you think about walking away?

00:11:39.380 --> 00:11:41.730
It wouldn't be the appropriate thing to do.

00:11:41.730 --> 00:11:43.100
I feel like I would be abandoning

00:11:43.100 --> 00:11:45.290
my friends, my family.

00:11:45.290 --> 00:11:48.770
Aaron Parker banks has been the only doctor on that battlefield

00:11:48.770 --> 00:11:51.800
at this family clinic in Owingsville, 50 miles east

00:11:51.800 --> 00:11:52.760
of Lexington.

00:11:52.760 --> 00:11:57.050
At any moment, if I start thinking about it, I cry.

00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:59.570
One of my mentors growing up, who was like a mom to me,

00:11:59.570 --> 00:12:01.310
she lost her battle.

00:12:01.310 --> 00:12:04.730
There's not even words that can describe what all we've seen

00:12:04.730 --> 00:12:06.780
over the last year and a half.

00:12:06.780 --> 00:12:09.860
He says finding those words and his own time to heal

00:12:09.860 --> 00:12:11.900
will have to wait for now.

00:12:11.900 --> 00:12:15.890
Kris Van Cleave, CBS News, Owingsville, Kentucky.

