00:16:51.650 --> 00:16:54.790


00:16:54.790 --> 00:16:56.680
It's been nearly a half a century

00:16:56.680 --> 00:16:58.840
since there was even a chance of snow

00:16:58.840 --> 00:17:00.400
in the Tampa, Florida, area.

00:17:00.400 --> 00:17:05.680
Well, today, on On the Road has a 100% chance of smiles.

00:17:05.680 --> 00:17:07.090
Steve Hartman has the story.

00:17:07.090 --> 00:17:09.680


00:17:09.680 --> 00:17:12.370
It all started here at Southshore Charter Academy

00:17:12.370 --> 00:17:14.950
outside Tampa when teacher Robin Hughes

00:17:14.950 --> 00:17:16.330
opened a book about snow--

00:17:16.330 --> 00:17:16.960
It's cold.

00:17:16.960 --> 00:17:18.940
--and got a frosty reception.

00:17:18.940 --> 00:17:21.130
They just had this perplexed look on their face.

00:17:21.130 --> 00:17:23.380
Then that's when I asked the question, how many of you

00:17:23.380 --> 00:17:24.970
all have never seen snow before?

00:17:24.970 --> 00:17:26.050
Hands shot up--

00:17:26.050 --> 00:17:26.590
A lot of you.

00:17:26.590 --> 00:17:28.750
--in classroom after classroom.

00:17:28.750 --> 00:17:30.250
Yeah, I've never seen snow.

00:17:30.250 --> 00:17:32.500
I saw it on a TV show.

00:17:32.500 --> 00:17:33.710
Like, Ice Age, it has snow.

00:17:33.710 --> 00:17:35.980
Like, what is snow, people?

00:17:35.980 --> 00:17:39.460
Clearly, Robin had tapped into a desperate yearning

00:17:39.460 --> 00:17:40.930
that she wanted to satisfy.

00:17:40.930 --> 00:17:41.600
Good.

00:17:41.600 --> 00:17:46.780
Unfortunately, it hasn't snowed in Central Florida in 45 years.

00:17:46.780 --> 00:17:50.410
Still, Robin wasn't about to let a little thing like meteorology

00:17:50.410 --> 00:17:51.650
get in her way.

00:17:51.650 --> 00:17:54.160
So she reached out to her sister in Kentucky

00:17:54.160 --> 00:17:56.470
and went full out frozen.

00:17:56.470 --> 00:17:59.170
She asked me if I want to build a snowman.

00:17:59.170 --> 00:18:02.320
Amber Estes begrudgingly agreed to ship her sister

00:18:02.320 --> 00:18:03.550
this snowman.

00:18:03.550 --> 00:18:06.400
And I said if he makes it to Tampa,

00:18:06.400 --> 00:18:08.560
his name is going to be Lucky.

00:18:08.560 --> 00:18:09.190
He made it.

00:18:09.190 --> 00:18:10.580
He made it.

00:18:10.580 --> 00:18:11.410
Meet Lucky.

00:18:11.410 --> 00:18:12.680
He made it.

00:18:12.680 --> 00:18:14.390
I was so excited when I opened the box.

00:18:14.390 --> 00:18:17.420
I mean, I could not wait to go in the classroom with them.

00:18:17.420 --> 00:18:21.680
So more than a month now, Lucky has been leaving the cafeteria

00:18:21.680 --> 00:18:26.270
freezer ever so briefly to grant these poor snow-deprived

00:18:26.270 --> 00:18:28.090
children their first ever opportunity--

00:18:28.090 --> 00:18:29.120
--make us happy.

00:18:29.120 --> 00:18:33.260
--to see, feel, and gush over the mini-miracle

00:18:33.260 --> 00:18:34.240
that is a snowman.

00:18:34.240 --> 00:18:36.110
It's real snow.

00:18:36.110 --> 00:18:37.730
And as a teacher, that's what you want.

00:18:37.730 --> 00:18:39.410
You just want that joy.

00:18:39.410 --> 00:18:42.530
It's like the first time I ever saw a snowman.

00:18:42.530 --> 00:18:44.180
And I was like--

00:18:44.180 --> 00:18:48.240
First time I met Lucky, I said he's handsome like a boy.

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:48.740
Yes.

00:18:48.740 --> 00:18:52.730
Perhaps no one is more smitten than five-year-old Momo.

00:18:52.730 --> 00:18:54.320
I love him.

00:18:54.320 --> 00:18:56.210
I knew I would kiss him.

00:18:56.210 --> 00:18:57.590
I knew it.

00:18:57.590 --> 00:18:59.420
Is that the first boy you've wanted to kiss?

00:18:59.420 --> 00:19:00.020
Yes.

00:19:00.020 --> 00:19:02.960
And the second boy I'm going to kiss is my dad.

00:19:02.960 --> 00:19:03.590
OK, good.

00:19:03.590 --> 00:19:04.090
All right.

00:19:04.090 --> 00:19:06.320
[LAUGHS]

00:19:06.320 --> 00:19:10.880
Bubbling joy, wide-eyed wonder, only a teacher

00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:14.360
could take a pile of snow, sticks, and a vegetable

00:19:14.360 --> 00:19:18.440
and somehow melt your heart.

00:19:18.440 --> 00:19:23.780
Steve Hartman on the road in Riverview, Florida.

00:19:23.780 --> 00:19:26.540
I'll never take snow for granted again.

00:19:26.540 --> 00:19:27.320
Nice story.

